 matthias haase wrote rh ships the code with the bytecode hinter disabled which makes non aa fonts really ugly this reqiures only a small change for include freetype config ftoption h it is very well documented red hat ships with the bytecode hinter enabled i think may have as well the enabling change to ftoption h is made by red hat s srpm before building take a look at freetype enable ft bci patch from the srpm it s pretty clear that this does exactly what needs to be done so if your fonts look ugly lack of bytecode hinting is not the cause rpm list mailing list http lists freshrpms net mailman listinfo rpm list 